column5: What a Nov day..........................trollin', trollin' trollin' on th rivuh.................
I knew I stayed up late for a special fishing report.  Nice one Harold.

I'm jealous. Catching was a bonus eh? Look at that sky, not a cloud. Nice, nice.  Why did I put the boat away Nov 1st, duh. The best November weather I can ever remember, ever. When I was working I always went south for 2 weeks at least. Cold, wet, damp, windy, flurries, freezing rain, snow. Yuck. This is central California weather without the rain.
good catch! it sure would have been a great day to be on the water

Just a leisurely aft out for a paddle with my wife dragging a Rapala behind----caught 3 small pike as well. A lot better than 2 hard days fishing with my buddy recently.  . My wife is not interested in going back out today, though, for some reason??!

Just a leisurely aft out for a paddle with my wife dragging a Rapala behind----caught 3 small pike as well. A lot better than 2 hard days fishing with my buddy recently.  . My wife is not interested in going back out today, though, for some reason??!   Not sure why. LOL  I lasted 2 hours. That was enough for me. Bloody line was flying off the pin.LOL
Short and sweet report. Is that a bow?
As dutch said.  I enjoyed it. Not every report needs 8 thousand pictures and 10 page write up.  I seen a nice fish, a canoe, nice weather and a happy angler...  10/10 in my book?
Beauty! Just the way every November day should be,
Nice day to get out and a fish to boot good job.   Art

10/10 in my book   You're being far too kind. The Moosey reports and the Borgerman's reports get a full 10. Gimme a 6 and I'll be happy!  BTW--thx to the mod(s) for deleting that political sideswipe from another member.

As dutch said.  I enjoyed it. Not every report needs 8 thousand pictures and 10 page write up.  I seen a nice fish, a canoe, nice weather and a happy angler...  10/10 in my book I actually prefer this style of report. Tell me what it is, how big it is, how you caught it and when, then show me a picture and I'm more than happy. I don't need to know what you ate, what brand the coffee was, or how many loons you saw on the lake.
